        <p>
          There are not many cleaning companies in North Alabama and Middle Tennessee that meet the bar of "insured, vetted, professional, won't disappear after the first visit." Two of them are MaidPro of Huntsville (and its sister Decatur location that covers Athens and Madison) and us — The Valley Clean Team.
        </p>

        <p>
          We get asked about MaidPro almost every week. Customers will text us a number from MaidPro and ask if we can match it, or they'll mention they're switching from MaidPro and want to know what we do differently. So we decided to write the honest version of this comparison instead of letting the question hang.
        </p>

        <p>
          This is not a hit piece on MaidPro. MaidPro Huntsville is an established Huntsville franchise that has earned the trust of plenty of North Alabama families. We're not here to talk you out of MaidPro.
        </p>

        <p>
          We're here to give you the straight comparison so you can decide which one fits your home and your situation. Some customers will read this and book MaidPro. That's fine. The ones who book us will know exactly what they're getting.
        </p>

        <h2>Quick verdict (the bottom line)</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>Choose MaidPro Huntsville if:</strong> You want a franchise-backed cleaning service with the infrastructure that a national brand provides. You're fine with a phone consult and same-day-to-next-day quote turnaround. You're in Huntsville, Madison, Athens, Decatur, or the surrounding Huntsville-area towns.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Choose The Valley Clean Team if:</strong> You want a 2-hour quote with no in-home walkthrough, photo proof of every clean sent to your phone, and the owner (Todd or Christen) answering the phone when you call. You want the same team every single visit. Or you're in the Shoals, Mountain Brook, Birmingham, or Nashville — where MaidPro is not local.
        </p>

        <p>Now the long version, market by market.</p>

        <h2>Side-by-side comparison</h2>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
          <table class="min-w-full text-sm border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b-2 border-gray-300">
